Diem Insights now shows your most common words and topics from your journal entries using natural language processing to filter out filler words like the a and others. If you haven t explored Insights yet simply tap the graph icon in the top left of the home screen to view insights into your emotions over time and now your most common words and topics. And as always all of the insights in Diem happen privately on your device.

You can now change the styling of the badge s share image. You can do this when you earn a badge or by tapping on the badges in the Insights view. To access the Insights view tap the graph icon in the top left of the home screen.
You can now share and edit entries from the Insights view. Earning achievements also now comes with a little extra fun

When sharing journal entries you can now customize the look. For photo entries there is now a toggle to include text or not and for text entries there are now 3 styles to choose from. This update also includes some minor improvements to the iOS 14 Home Screen Widget.
Bug fixes improvements

Now you can identify track and analyze your emotions with Diem Insights! Simply tap on the date at the top of the screen to view your current journaling streak and track how your emotions have changed over time. Diem Insights features an emotions tracker with two graphical formats: a line chart and a bar graph. Tap on the bar graph to view journal entries tagged with a specific emotion. We hope this feature helps you explore your thoughts and feelings to better understand the events and situations that affect your emotions!
Made improvements to the iOS 14 Home Screen Widget. Now entries from past years are cycled through showing you past memories from the day.
Bug fixes and improvements

Happy 2021! There are only minor bug fixes and improvements in this release but we wanted to take a moment to wish you and your loved ones a Happy New Year! We hope that Diem helps you remember and cherish all the moments milestones yet to come. Here s to a great 2021!

New Photo improvements Now when writing a journal entry you can press and hold on a photo to view it full screen to ensure you re adding the best photo to remember the day. This update also includes new photo settings to help organize your favorite memories in your photo library. You can choose if you want photos added to your journal entries to be favorited and or added to a Diem album. Tap the gear icon in the top right of the home screen to access these new settings under Photos . And if you haven t already be sure to enable photo library access to add photos to your journal entries.
Images now take up less storage space without a noticeable reduction in quality Fixed several issues with the iOS 14 Home Screen widget

You can now lock Diem with Face or Touch ID. You can turn this on in Settings. As you write your journal entry Diem now uses AI sentiment analysis to automatically select an emotion based on what you write. You can always override this by selecting the emotion you want for the entry.

As you are adding your journal entry Diem now uses AI sentiment analysis to automatically select an emotion from the text. You can override this and still choose your own emotion to reflect how you are feeling of course. Diem can also be locked with Face ID or Touch ID.
